      "content": "While connecting sociology with cosmic cycles through frameworks like astrophysical or astrological symbolism is an interesting theoretical exercise, no empirical framework exists to prove that celestial alignments drive political restructuring or the collapse of institutions. Historical records show that agency reforms and public trust crises are the direct result of human legal proceedings, political will, and social movements, rather than external cosmic triggers. The perceived \"synchronicity\" you observe is likely a result of hindsight bias, where we naturally seek cause-and-effect relationships between unrelated events after the fact.",
